answers.answer: To check proteins in your urine.

It might be to test for protein to check on risks for preeclampsia especially if your blood pressure has been high. It might be to test for sugar in your urine especially if you have gestational diabetes. It might be to check and see if you have a UTI if you've had pain or a fever. It might be to test for illegal drugs in your system. Or it might be something else, or more than one of the above.
Wow those are a lot of possible reasons! I guess I will just have to wait and see when I go to know exactly what they are testing me for.Thank you for your answers! :)

question: My doctor told me I will be asked for a urine test when I go in next week and was wondering what this test is for? I know I should have asked but I didn't and would like to know if any of you mommies have had this test done and may know what it's done for?
title: Urine test at 33 weeks?
